SHAM SINGH, alias Seam Singh, etc., Appellant, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Appellee. No. 8063. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 19, 1936. Marshall B. Woodworth, of San Francisco, Cal., and S. Luke Howe, of Sacramento, Cal., for appellant. H. H. McPike, U. S. Atty., of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellee, ordered, appeal dismissed, for failure of appellant to print record and file brief; mandate forthwith.
